<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                    <head>No. 195.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Daggett</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-12-13"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 13,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 43.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Adverting to the instruction sent to you upon
                        the 15th ultimo, No. 38, I have now to transmit, for your information, the
                        inclosed copies of correspondence between the Hawaiian minister here and
                        myself, touching the complaint of the Pacific Mail Steamship Company against
                        the Government of Hawaii.</p>
                    <p>The Department’s reply to Mr. Carter is sufficiently explicit to render any
                        special instructions to you in the premises unnecessary.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>